    "summary": "250+ barrel re-exports mapped. Consumers will import directly from: (1) @mohasinac/appkit subtree for generic UI/hooks/utils, (2) local @/ paths for app-specific components/hooks/utils, (3) @/contexts for providers, (4) feature packages for domain logic."
  },
  "migrationNotes": {
    "componentMigration": "All @mohasinac/appkit/ui exports stay in @mohasinac/appkit/ui. Local components (Button, Input, etc.) remain in src/components/* subdirectories. Imports change: `import { Button } from '@/components'` → `import Button from '@/components/ui/Button'` or `import { Button } from '@/components/ui'` (if keeping subdir barrels).",
    "hookMigration": "All @mohasinac/appkit/react exports (useSwipe, useGesture, etc.) stay there. Local hooks remain in src/hooks/. Consumers import either directly from @mohasinac/appkit/react or @/hooks/<hookName>. Subdir barrels (src/hooks/index.ts) can be kept for convenience.",
    "utilsMigration": "All generic @mohasinac/appkit/utils, @mohasinac/appkit/validation, @mohasinac/appkit/security exports remain there. App-specific utils (business-day, guest-cart, id-generators) stay in src/utils/. Consumers import from @mohasinac/appkit/* or @/utils/* directly.",
    "appkitAlignment": "This mapping ensures letitrip.in consumes @mohasinac/appkit as published npm package without barrel re-exports. All app-local code (src/components/*, src/hooks/*, src/utils/*) is imported directly from subdirs.",
    "deprecationPath": "Step 1: Update all import statements in src/ to use direct paths (optional subdir barrels). Step 2: Delete root barrel files (src/index.ts, src/components/index.ts, etc.) only after verification. Step 3: Update app docs/guides to reflect direct import pattern."
  },
